subject: p19759491
Findings: In comparison with the study of, there is still enlargement of the cardiac silhouette with some elevation of pulmonary venous pressure, though substantially less than on the prior study. The more focal opacification at the left base is not appreciated at this time. There is fluid within one of the major fissures, though no substantial free pleural effusion.
